### HYMN CXIX

#### A prayer for release from debts incurred without intention of payment

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_0611901">1</span></span>The debt
which I incur, not gaming, Agni! and, not intending  
   to repay, acknowledge, <span id="page_a256">p. a256</span>  
  That may Vaisvānara, the best, our sovran, carry away into the  
   world of virtue.  
<span class="margnote"><span id="an_0611902">2</span></span>I cause
Vaisvānara to know, confessing the debt whose payment  
   to the Gods is promised.  
  He knows to tear asunder all these nooses: so may we dwell  
   with him the gentle-minded.  
<span class="margnote"><span id="an_0611903">3</span></span>Vaisvānara
the Purifier purge me when I oppose their hope and  
   break my promise,  
  Unknowing in my heart. With supplication, whatever guilt there  
   is in that, I banish.

